<TITLE> Family, with toddler, killed in Khulna bike tragedy </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Alip Ghatak and Shubir Roy bdnews24.com correspondent Khulna/Bagerhat, August 6 (bdnews24.com)  A family of three, including a four year-old child, were killed on Thursday when a pick-up van rammed into their motor cycle in Khulna. Khulna police officer Monirul Islam identified the victims as Andru Ashish Haldar, 40, area manager of a private organisation Heed Bangladesh, his wife Istera Haldar, 35, a school teacher of Home of Joy School in Rupsha and their only child Abanti, 4, who was a student of the same school. "Ashish was dropping his wife Istera and their child Abanti at the school by motorcycle," said Islam. "Istera and Abanti were killed on the spot when a pick-up van ran into them from behind as they were crossing the Khanjahan Ali Bridge from Khulna to Rupsha Upazila." Ashish died after being taken to hospital, said Islam. Headmaster of Home of Joy School, Jhon Antony Sarjon, said the family lived in the town's Khanjahan Ali Road. "Ashish brought his wife and child to the school every day," said Sarjon. The dead bodies were being kept at the Khulna Medical College Hospital morgue, said police. bdnews24.c
